<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 7:30PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern
Meriwether, west central Upson and northwestern Talbot Counties
through 800 PM EDT...
At 730 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Woodland, or 10 miles
north of Talbotton. This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Manchester, Woodland, Sunset Village, Sprewell Bluff State Park,
Pleasant Hill and Flint Hill.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
